I agree with a lot of what has been said.  The biggest change I would ask for is that mobs get no more than 10 spells total they can cast.   yeah, they can have 2 extra from us, but having the ability to cast every spell from 1 - xx lvl they could cast is kinda cheap.   <br>
<br>
As far as my perception of the change?   I like it.  I have not been in OS hunting, but I do fight casters fairly often.   3 of my favorite hunting spots have casters in them.   Which, gives me a nervous excitement about going back to them.   The most fun I have is when I live through and overcome what should kill me.    My best memories are of these fights.  <br>
<br>
I now have a measure of trepidation when I know I will be fighting casters.   I do over buff.  I take the time to be buffed, and get what I need.    I even was sacrificing AC for resists last night on some encounters.   Why?  because I wanted to be overly safe. <br>
<br>
I consider it to be a new game of sorts now.   Relearning what mobs can and cannot do.   Slowly crawling through a dungeon, killing the greenies you would normaly invis past to save time.   Why?  to see just how much the yard trash will hurt as a measurement of what the Blues will do.  <br>
<br>
Right now, I like the changes.   I do think there is some tuning to be done to bring it a bit more in line, but so far, it is quite interesting.<br>
