<br>
I remember back when I was in about my 30's I would try and stay away from caster mobs, because they hit so hard and could cast.  Fighting stuff in FM with my bard friend, if we aggroed a caster most of the time we would just zone, because they where not worth the trouble.<br>
<br>
I would like the changes more if they made the caster more in line with how PCs are.  Obvisouly dont give them PC level melee and hit points, but have the ratio similar.  So if a PC caster has on average 40% less HP than a melee, then a caster NPC should have about 40% less hp than a NPC mob.  Maybe it doesnt have to be exact, but somewhat similar.  That would be a big improvement.<br>
<br>
Basically what they have done is totaly messed up the balance by making all caster NPC much harder.<br>
<br>
However even with these changes, it is still easier to level than it was back in the day.  40% exp penalty, unbalance 2h weps, small mana pool, that thing that re set attack when you would cast a spell.....Im only 59 (and lots of these thing were fixed when I was mid levels), anyone who made it 60 with all those issues (not to mention way crappier gear) deserves some serious respect.  Complaining that game is too hard to level now is nuts and insulting to those people who leveled when it really was hard, IMO. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzarraa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zarraa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/7/02 9:40:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=366.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Here we go again...</span><hr size=1> I thought we were past that stage If you read my above post I apologized. My outburst was both Irrational and out of line. I do however see the God complex emerging in some of these posts. I really, really, really don't care if you find it &quot;hard to take my complaints seriously&quot; because I didn't start EQ in March of 99 I'm speaking on what affects me now. I have many friends who are ubber level and still have humility. To those I've offended I apologize again but I Bow down to No one.<br>
