<br>
Caster MOBs have always been a joke if single pulled. And lets face it, for your average group single pulling or crowd control is well practiced. Arcane casters drop faster and hit for less than warrior MOBs.<br>
<br>
I don't think there should be any reduction in their AC or damage. If that was done a full group could drop them before they got more than two or three spells off.<br>
<br>
I also think the idea of MOBs being able to land spells on higher level PCs is a good idea. By reducing the 'level' based effect on resists, you can take some of the 'easy money' out of bottom feeding/farming without upping the danger level for PCs of the appropriate levels. Lets face it, if a very green MOB is casting on you, then 90% of the time you've done something directly to it.<br>
<br>
BTW, I do agree that some long time lvl 60s start over ( make an alt, don't delete anyone <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), but for a much nicer reason. A lot of content and power has been added to the game. The days of a crowded SOLa are long gone, but that just means there are a lot of dungoens/zones that brave parties can battle through in peace. There are a lot of wonderfull lowbie zones now and you don't know what you're missing (bring friends though, dungeon groups are hard to find).<br>
